page.title: 15BIRDS
page.content: THE{BIRDS}MOST COMMONLY SEEN IN GARDENS AND THE VICINITY OF {DRAYCOTT} ARE{HOUSE SPARROWS, ROBINS, WRENS, {SONG THRUSHES,BLACKBIRDS, BLUE AND {GREAT TITS, CHAFFINCHES, COLLARED {DOVES, DUNNOCKS,GREEN WOODPECKERS AND {STARLINGS.}DURING THE SUMMER MONTHS {SWALLOWS,SWIFTS AND HOUSE MARTINS}NEST AROUND THE BUILDINGS. THE BAD WEATHER BRINGS THE MORE UNUSUAL BIRDS INTO THE GARDENS E.G.{REED BUNTING,BLACKCAP, {REDWING AND MISSEL THRUSH.}THE BIRDS USUALLY FOUND ON DRAYCOTT MOOR AND HILL SLOPES ARE{GREY HERON,LAPWING, {MALLARD, MUTE SWAN,SNIPE,MOORHEN, {COMMON BUZZARD,KESTREL,SPARROW HAWK, {TAWNY OWL,LITTLE OWL, BARN OWL AND {CUCKOO.}AS WELL AS THE{CORVIDS,CROW, {ROOK, JACKDAW AND MAGPIE THE GREY {WAGTAIL, CHIFF CHAFF, COAL TIT AND {LONG TAILED TIT}CAN BE OBSERVED.
